Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and sliced into 1-inch-thick wedges); mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Toss Brussels sprouts and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}(divided) (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @dried rosemary{1%teaspoon}, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat if pork begins to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{} and cover with #foil{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium-low heat. Add minced onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add minced garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @apricot jam{1%unit} and @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}; cook until syrupy, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4); cook until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork and Brussels sprout and onion jumble between plates. Spoon sauce over pork and serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.